            "text": "KLIA Ekspres"
          }
        ]
      },
      "description": {
        "localized_texts": [
          {
            "language_code": "en",
            "text": "Express Rail Link (ERL) is the operator of KLIA Ekspres and KLIA Transit train services that connect Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KLIA & KLIA2) and the city. The non-stop 57-km journey on KLIA Ekspres between KL Sentral and KLIA takes only 28 minutes. Passengers can also take a 3-minute ride between KLIA2 and KLIA. The KLIA Transit service stops at three intermediate stations i.e. Bandar Tasik Selatan, Putrajaya & Cyberjaya and Salak Tinggi. ERL has been recognised locally and internationally for consistently providing high standards in the air-rail services industry. ERL was named AirRail Link of the Year at the Global AirRail Awards in 2012, 2014, 2015 and 2016. On the home front, ERL was awarded the Best Operator (Railway) in 2017 by the Land Public Transport Commission of Malaysia (SPAD). To date, ERL has carried more than 90 million passengers.KLIA Ekspres:- Fastest way to the city- Frequent train departures - WiFi onboard - Free porter service on availability - Easy connection from KL Sentral Station to anywhere in the cityAirline Check-in at KL City Air Terminal (KL CAT) in KL Sentral is currently not available"
          }
        ]
      },
      "rating": {
        "average_value": 4.3,
        "rating_count": 100
      },
